            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "After digging more, it seems a buffer-local pattern in a comma-separated aupat may cause other patterns to be ignored:\n`:new | au BufEnter <buffer=1>,<buffer=2> \"`\n\nNvim:\n```\n--- Autocommands ---\nBufEnter\n    <buffer=1>\n              \"\n```\n\nVim:\n```\n--- Autocommands ---\nBufEnter\n    <buffer=1>\n              \"\n    <buffer=2>\n              \"\n```\n\nI'll try to look into these parsing issues before 0.12. (but leave the API bugfix until after) (#37051)",
